        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): default memorySearch provider to \"auto\" instead of \"openai\"",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAfter upgrading to 2026.6.1, the `memorySearch` provider silently resets to `\"openai\"` when no provider is explicitly configured. Previously (2026.5.26) the default was `\"auto\"`, which correctly auto-selected an available embedding provider (e.g. `gemini-embedding-001` for Google AI Studio users).\n\nThe regression was introduced in commit `4d89e00c50` (\"feat(embeddings): add OpenAI-compatible core provider (#85269)\") which hardcoded the unresolved default to `\"openai\"` (`DEFAULT_MEMORY_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER`), bypassing the auto-select mechanism.\n\nFixes #90787\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: memorySearch provider silently defaults to \"openai\" when not configured, instead of \"auto\"\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node v24.13.1, Linux\n\n## Exact steps or command run after fix\n\n```bash\npnpm test -- src/agents/memory-search.test.ts\n```\n\n## After-fix evidence\n\n```\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  35 passed (35)\n```\n\n## Observed result after the fix\n\nAll 35 tests pass, including the updated expectation that unconfigured `memorySearch.provider` defaults to `\"auto\"` (not `\"openai\"`):\n\n- `defaults provider to auto when unspecified` — verified: `resolved.provider` is `\"auto\"`\n- `preserves explicit auto provider config` — verified: explicit `\"auto\"` is preserved\n- All `resolve explicit concrete providers` tests still pass: `\"openai\"`, `\"local\"`, `\"none\"`, custom providers all behave correctly\n\n## What was not tested\n\nEnd-to-end verification with actual embedding providers (Google AI Studio, OpenAI) was not performed because it requires live API keys. The fix is validated at the config-resolution unit test level, which is the layer where the regression was introduced.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n| Test Type | Result | Details |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| Unit Tests | ✅ | 35/35 passed |\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**Yes** — users who did not configure `memorySearch.provider` will now get `\"auto\"` behavior (auto-select available provider) instead of being forced to `\"openai\"`. This restores the 2026.5.26 behavior. Users who explicitly configured a provider are unaffected.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**No** — only the unconfigured default value changed; all explicit configurations are preserved identically.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**No** — this is a config-layer default value change only.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- Users who explicitly set `provider: \"openai\"` are unaffected.\n- Users who explicitly set `provider: \"auto\"` are unaffected (the value is now preserved through the config layer instead of being resolved at config time).\n- The only behavioral change is for users with no `provider` setting — they regain auto-select functionality.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- All existing unit tests pass, including explicit provider configuration tests.\n- The change is a one-line default value restoration.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-90787-memorysearch-provider-silently-resets-to-openai-after-upgrade",
